"title='Raising Beacons without UDRLs and Teaching them How to Sleep | Naksyn’s blog' description='UDRLs and prepended loaders aren’t the only way to execute a raw payload and get a direct hooking in place. In the case of Cobalt Strike, a generic PE loader can be tweaked to execute an UDRL-less Beacon and get direct hooking for an easier prototyping of Sleep obfuscation techniques. Using this approach, two techniques that bypasses the Elastic’s RX -> RW Sleep detection, along with few other scanners, are then demonstrated.' url='https://naksyn.com/cobalt%20strike/2024/07/02/raising-beacons-without-UDRLs-teaching-how-to-sleep.html' language='en-US' keywords=None robots=None og_title='Raising Beacons without UDRLs and Teaching them How to Sleep' og_description='UDRLs and prepended loaders aren’t the only way to execute a raw payload and get a direct hooking in place. In the case of Cobalt Strike, a generic PE loader can be tweaked to execute an UDRL-less Beacon and get direct hooking for an easier prototyping of Sleep obfuscation techniques. Using this approach, two techniques that bypasses the Elastic’s RX -> RW Sleep detection, along with few other scanners, are then demonstrated.' og_url='http://0.0.0.0:4000/cobalt%20strike/2024/07/02/raising-beacons-without-UDRLs-teaching-how-to-sleep.html' og_image=None og_audio=None og_determiner=None og_locale='en_US' og_locale_alternate=None og_site_name='Naksyn’s blog' og_video=None favicon=None dc_terms_created=None dc_date_created=None dc_date=None dc_terms_type=None dc_type=None dc_terms_audience=None dc_terms_subject=None dc_subject=None dc_description=None dc_terms_keywords=None modified_time=None published_time='2024-07-02T00:00:00-04:00' article_tag=None article_section=None source_url='https://naksyn.com/cobalt%20strike/2024/07/02/raising-beacons-without-UDRLs-teaching-how-to-sleep.html' status_code=200 scrape_id='019c706d-8dd4-759e-8d1f-45fcd5233ac5' num_pages=None content_type='text/html' proxy_used='basic' timezone